post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_24771148_24771182_0": {"length": 32, "quality": 0.9696969696969697, "section_id": 411}}, "n3337": {"so_24771148_24771182_0": {"length": 32, "quality": 0.9696969696969697, "section_id": 402}}, "n4659": {"so_24771148_24771182_0": {"length": 32, "quality": 0.9696969696969697, "section_id": 429}}}, "24771148": {"ViewCount": "92", "Body": "<p>The code below is:</p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt;\nusing namespace std;\n\nclass A\n{\npublic:\n    A() {}\n    ~A()\n    {\n        cout &lt;&lt; \"in destructor\" &lt;&lt; endl;\n    }\n};\nvoid main()\n{\n    A a;\n    a.~A();\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>has the following output:</p>\n<pre><code>in destructor\nin destructor\n</code></pre>\n<p>Why my app does not crash if the destructed object is destructed again?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "24771182", "Title": "Why my program does not crash if destructor is called twice", "CreationDate": "2014-07-16T02:13:34.580", "Id": "24771148", "CommentCount": "2", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2014-07-16T02:25:50.613", "Score": "0", "OwnerUserId": "163394", "Tags": "<c++>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "24771182": {"Id": "24771182", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>C++ Standard, section \u00a7 12.4 [destructors]</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_24771148_24771182_0\">Once a destructor is invoked for an object, the object no longer exists; <strong>the behavior is undefined if the destructor is invoked for an object whose lifetime has ended</strong> ( 3.8 ). [ Example: if the destructor for an automatic object is explicitly invoked, and the block is subsequently left in a manner that would ordinarily invoke implicit destruction of the object, the behavior is undefined.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So your program has <em>undefined behavior</em>, it could crash now, later, never, earth could stop spinning etc... don't do it.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>void main()</code> must be <code>int main()</code></li>\n</ul>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "3510483", "LastActivityDate": "2014-07-16T02:25:50.613", "Score": "6", "CreationDate": "2014-07-16T02:19:40.947", "ParentId": "24771148", "CommentCount": "7", "OwnerUserId": "3510483", "LastEditDate": "2014-07-16T02:25:50.613"}});